# Restore YouTube-Style Grids

The objective is to revert the "Bento Grid" layout experiments in favor of a standard, high-fidelity YouTube-style grid. This will improve familiarity and content density while maintaining the premium "VibeStream" visual language.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> I am removing the full-width "Hero" section from the Home Feed to ensure a consistent grid density from the top of the page, matching the YouTube experience.

## Proposed Changes

### UI & Layout

#### [MODIFY] [HomeClient.tsx](file:///C:/GOLive/app/HomeClient.tsx)
- Remove the featured "Hero" section at the top.
- Standardize the grid configuration (`grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 xl:grid-cols-4`).
- Remove "intermixed shorts shelf" for now to keep a clean video grid focus (or keep it as a standard row).

#### [MODIFY] [VideoCard.tsx](file:///C:/GOLive/components/VideoCard.tsx)
- Reduce border-radius from `32px` to a more standard `12px-16px` for a cleaner look.
- Refine metadata spacing to match YouTube's proportions.
- Remove `bento-card` styles that add excessive padding/shadows.

#### [MODIFY] [DashboardClient.tsx](file:///C:/GOLive/app/studio/dashboard/DashboardClient.tsx)
- Ensure the "Content Manager" table and grids follow the same standard grid logic if applicable.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- Run `npm run build` to ensure no regressions.

### Manual Verification
- Verify Home feed looks like a standard YouTube grid at multiple breakpoints (Desktop, Tablet, Mobile).
- Verify consistency between Home, Profile, and Search grids.
